    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for high offensive output today, anchored by **Kyle Tucker** (85.90) and **Gunnar Henderson** (81.77), our elite starters for the 2026-04-18 slate. **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a massive 14% park factor boost at Coors and a favorable matchup against the right-handed Feltner, pushing his efficiency score to our highest of the day. Meanwhile, **Gunnar Henderson** leads off with a projected 10% order bonus, and his dynamic platoon advantage against Williams provides the perfect catalyst for a high-volume day in Runs and SB. **Josh Lowe** and **Andy Pages** are critical secondary plays; **Josh Lowe** specifically benefits from M\u00e1rquez's slow delivery, which creates an optimized environment for our pursuit of scarce SB, while **Andy Pages** leverages the same Coors Field park factor advantage as **Kyle Tucker** to maintain a strong 74.43 score.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Nasim Nunez**, who finished with a 57.95, just narrowly missing the cut behind **Luis Robert Jr.** (57.98). While **Nasim Nunez** offers the switch-hitting versatility and sprint speed we covet, the efficiency gap was closed by the defensive catching metrics against Houser; specifically, the catcher\u2019s elite pop-time against the base paths neutralized the upside **Nasim Nunez** would otherwise provide in the SB category. Elsewhere, we are monitoring **Jackson Merrill** (56.24) and **Drake Baldwin** (48.10) closely, as both face left-handed opposition in Kikuchi and S\u00e1nchez, respectively. While **Jackson Merrill** remains a start, his 13% platoon penalty highlights the necessity of tracking lineup adjustments as the afternoon progresses. Despite the overall favorable projections for our rostered players like **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, we must remain vigilant regarding these platoon-heavy matchups to ensure we maximize our daily game caps without sacrificing our standing in the AVG category.",
